      document.getElementById("ai44").innerHTML = "<p><b>SCP FOUNDATION OVERSEER COUNCIL INVESTIGATION</b><br><b>Case #:</b> ID-908734 (04-01-2020)<br>…<br><b>Addendum 14:</b> Text Exchanges with Serpent’s Hand<br><b>Description:</b> Throughout the development phase of “Pageturn,” Dr. Rovēros Prometheus and a Serpent’s Hand operative – later identified as Dr. Oscar Stonefield - exchanged anonymous text messages using disposable “burner” cellphones. Prometheus’ phone was found underneath the floorboards of his home in ████ Rosewood Drive. The messages exchanged between the two individuals bring to light their conspiracy to expose top-secret information and thereby cause a Broken Masquerade scenario.<br>The following are examples of the text exchanges between Prometheus and Stonefield, highlighting the numerous violations of Foundation policy over the Project’s three-and-a-half year development.<br>…<br>(23/12/2019)<br><b>Oscar Stonefield:</b> Where are you?<br><b>Rovēros Prometheus:</b> Chamber 29B, just like we planned, why?<br><b>OS:</b> Change of plans. I’m looking at the Beacon and there seems to be a cable that’s been damaged, probably from a storm or something. We’ll have to postpone until this is fixed.<br><b>RP:</b> Which one?<br><b>OS:</b> One of the fiber optic cables. Unless we want our message to be jumbled and incomprehensible, we’ll have to reschedule.<br><b>RP:</b> That’s odd. I just checked the Beacon a couple days ago and everything seemed fine.<br><b>RP:</b> I didn’t hear of any storms coming through the area recently. Was there one?<br><b>OS:</b> Fine, you got me. Should’ve known you’d check everything for yourself.<br><b>RP:</b> I actually didn’t, but you just confirmed everything I needed to know.<br><b>RP:</b> You’re not getting cold feet are you?<br><b>OS:</b> I guess I just thought we would have more time, you know?<br><b>OS:</b> These past few months just flew by… now that we’re here, I’m realizing this is all easier said than done.<br><b>RP:</b> Really wish you’d brought this up earlier before I got everything set up.<br><b>RP:</b> But if we really, really must, we can postpone if you don’t think you’re ready.<br><b>OS:</b> I mean, I think we’re ready to do this, don’t get me wrong.<br><b>OS:</b> It’s the other thing I’m worried about.<br><b>RP:</b> I see.<br><b>RP:</b> Listen, we’ve been through this, I’ll be fine.<br><b>RP:</b> No matter what they do to me, I’ll be alright knowing our plan worked.<br><b>OS:</b> But I won’t, Rovēros!<br><b>OS:</b> I’ve completely taken these years we’ve had together for granted. Nearly three years, and not once did I think about the repercussions of what we were doing.<br><b>OS:</b> I don’t want to do this anymore, Rovēros.<br><b>RP:</b> Trust me, I’m feeling quite nervous about all this myself.<br><b>RP:</b> But I also know that this is sometimes the cost of freedom. Sacrifice.<br><b>RP:</b> Tell me, if you could sacrifice yourself – not necessarily death, but a sacrifice – to change the world for the better, would you?<br><b>OS:</b> Of course.<br><b>RP:</b> Right. That’s what I thought.<br><b>RP:</b> Plus, I hope you can take comfort in the fact that these past few years with you were the best years of my life.<br><b>RP:</b> Wherever I am, whatever they do to me, I’ll always think of you.<br><b>RP:</b> Tell you what: assuming they don’t kill me, if there’s ever an opportunity to escape, I’ll take it.<br><b>RP:</b> Then, we can be together again. OK?<br><b>OS:</b> … OK. I’ll still miss you.<br><b>RP:</b> Not as much as I’ll miss you.<br><b>RP:</b> Ready to do this?<br><b>OS:</b> … Yes. I’m ready.<br><b>OS:</b> I love you, Rovēros.<br><b>RP:</b> I love you too.<br>< END LOG ></p>";
    } else if (counter == 45) {
      document.getElementById("ai45").innerHTML = "<p>GLOBAL RIOTS ENSUE FOLLOWING MYSTERIOUS BROADCAST<br><br>Sat December 24, 2019<br><br>GNN – Chaos ensued after televisions worldwide were hijacked this morning with a bizarre yet ominous broadcast apparently revealing the nature of our reality. <br><br>The transmission, originating from a supposed “SCP Foundation” according to text displayed at the bottom of the screen, showed a live feed of numerous individuals, most of whom were typing on a computer with some writing traditionally with a pen and paper. <br><br>The controversy lies in what exactly these individuals were writing. The video feed showed they were composing stories strikingly similar to the present moment, regardless of where the transmission was sent, down to the most minute details as they were happening.<br><br>While the individual responsible for leaking the message is still currently unknown, people worldwide have gathered to protest and even riot in light of this event. The exact meaning of their anger, however, is unclear; while some protestors have demanded to know what other pertinent information is being hidden from them and who the “SCP Foundation” is, others seem to be simply wreaking havoc out of spite for their supposed lack of free will. Regardless, the ensuing chaos from the mysterious broadcast has many fearing for the future of humanity, and others have dubbed this a “Christmas from Hell.”<br><br>Stay tuned for more details as they are revealed.</p>";
    } else if (counter == 46) {
