Yes. You were steadfast, determined, not easily swayed by anyone else. What happened?<br><br><b>Prometheus:</b> I wasn’t steadfast, Zeke, I was blind. Ignorant. When I was younger I believed that knowledge should be made free, no matter how hard it is to swallow. Getting a Foundation job made me forget. Now I remember.<br><br><b>Usa:</b> Stop that, Rov. You’re better than this. You’re better than to just blindly accept Serpent’s Hand rhetoric, smarter than that. Which brings me to my next question –<br><br><i>Pause on the recording. Usa can be heard leaning forward in his seat.</i><br><br><b>Usa:</b> -- who could possibly be able to sway the unswayable Rovēros Prometheus into joining the Hand?<br><br><b>Prometheus:</b> Don’t remember.<br><br><b>Usa:</b> I know you have a photographic memory, so don’t give me that bullshit.<br><br><b>Prometheus:</b> Worth a shot.<br><br><b>Usa:</b> Dammit, Rovēros, stop with the games and tell me <i>who.</i><br><br><b>Prometheus:</b> I think you mean “whom.”<br><br><b>Usa:</b> … You understand there are consequences if you don’t answer, right?<br><br><b>Prometheus:</b> There’ll be consequences regardless. Might as well have fun with it and protect my friends while I’m at it.<br><br><b>Usa:</b> Alright, fuck it. Be uncooperative, see if I care. This is why I never liked you, truth be told. Know that we’ll find your special little friend, wherever they are, and we’ll give them the same fate we’ll give you.<br><br><b>Prometheus:</b> Oh? And what’s that?<br><br><b>Usa:</b> None of your fucking business, that’s what. <br><br><i>Silence on the recording.</i><br><br><b>Usa:</b> Actually… you might’ve just given me an idea.<br><br><b>Prometheus:</b> Glad I could help.<br><br><b>Usa:</b> You’ve given me an excuse to get a program concept off the ground with the Council. We’ll see how willing you are to inform once you’re the first test subject.<br><br><i>More silence.</i><br><br><b>Prometheus:</b> You’re not talking about…?<br><br><b>Usa:</b> Now I’ve got your attention.<br><br><i>Prometheus' breathing is audible on recording.</i><br><br><b>Prometheus:</b> Please, <i>please,</i> if you're going to do that to me, don't do it to him, <i>I'm begging you.</i><br><br><b>Usa:</b> I'm afraid <i>we</i> can do whatever the fuck we want.<br><br><i>A slight chuckle can be heard.</i><br><br><b>Usa:</b> You wanna be some fount of knowledge so badly? E.A.G.L.E. can arrange that.<br><br>< END LOG ></p>";
    } else if (counter == 47) {
      document.getElementById("ai47").innerHTML = "<p>Encyclopedic Algorithm with Grenwich-Lee Electromechanics (E.A.G.L.E.) Program Summary<br><br><b>Objective:</b> To develop a method of incarceration for high-level criminals that simultaneously ensures both secure imprisonment and beneficial use for the Foundation.<br><br><b>Description:</b> The E.A.G.L.E. Program, first proposed by Site-26 Director Ezekiel “Zeke” Usa, is an experimental incarceration alternative that utilizes Grenwich-Lee electromechanical cognition-database linking (“mind uploading”) technology. The program attaches a prisoner’s consciousness to a designated digital mainframe wherein he/she will act as a database intelligence application for Foundation personnel usage while he/she is “awake.” While “awake,” the prisoner will be provided very limited vocabulary and thought capabilities, limited only to the provided information in the Foundation database.<br><br>While “asleep” (i.e. when not in use by Foundation personnel), the subject will be put in a cognitive simulation designed to emotionally, physically, and psychologically strain him/her to their absolute limits. Any acts of rebellion (planning escape, concealing information, etc.) will be severely punished during the “sleeping” phase, which is designed to feel as though it lasts for hours or, in some cases, days at a time. An avatar of the Foundation is present is all “dreams” and is designed to indoctrinate the prisoner into obeying Foundation standards and quell future attempts of rebellion (known as the “E.A.G.L.E. Protocol”).<br><br>More information can be found <u>here</u></p>";
    } else if (counter == 48) {
